H0.text: Terminal velocity is what a skydiver will reach when the air drag equals their weight.

H1.text: Constant velocity is what a skydiver will reach when the air drag equals their weight.

H2.text: Building velocity is what a skydiver will reach when the air drag equals their weight.

H3.text: Ending velocity is what a skydiver will reach when the air drag equals their weight.

A4.text: At this point the object stops accelerating and continues falling at a constant speed called the terminal velocity.

A5.text: At equilibrium, the net force is zero (Fnet = 0) and the velocity becomes the terminal velocity.
